p.span: acid, cold, fire, necrotic, poison, radiant, slashing
If the Obsidian Tusker does not move on its turn, its Tusks attack deals double damage.
Attacks against the Obsidian Tusker from 30 ft. away or more are made at disadvantage. It has advantage on Stealth checks.
The Obsidian Tusker's Pestle attack deals double damage against objects and structures.

The Obsidian Tusker eats light. It requires at least 8 hours of normal light per day or suffer 1 level of exhaustion. It does not need to breathe, drink, eat, or rest—although it can get benefits from rests.
The Obsidian Tusker is immune to any effect that changes its form or appearance.
The Obsidian Tusker makes 1 Pestle attack and 1 Tusks attack.
+10 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target.
Tusks.The Obsidian Tusker attacks using 2 of its 6 tusks.
+10 to hit, reach 10 ft., one Large or larger creature, or two Medium or smaller creatures that are within 15 ft. of each other.

20 (2d12 + 7) piercing damage from each tusk. Each hit target must succeed a DC 15 Dexterity Saving Throw or be impaled (grappled) on a tusk. Each of the 6 tusks can have one creature impaled. Impaling a Large or larger creature takes 2 tusks.

If at least 1 target is impaled, the Obsidian Tusker can do a Death Roll and cause 31 slashing damage per tusk to the impaled target on that tusk. Each target is hurled away 1d12x5ft. in a random direction. A target that is hurled against an object or structure takes 7(2d6) bludgeoning damage.
After a Death Roll, the targets are no longer impaled (grappled).
